r=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 width=95%><tr><td bgcolor=#2f2f4f><table border=0 width=100% cellpadding=5 cellspacing=1><tr><td valign=top bgcolor=#222245 class=headings><font color=#FFFFFF>Author</font></td><td valign=top bgcolor=#222245 class=headings><font color=#FFFFFF>Comment</font></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/uwalkerbohh.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Walker Bohh</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Guild Leader</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(9/24/02 8:25:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/finfinitusvindicatfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=850.topic&index=81>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.infinitusvindicat.com/memberpics/iv-logo60x60.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: VP</span><hr size=1> I`m sure this is, by far, the longest post I`ve ever made.<br>
<br>
IV is reborn and I saw no reason nor need to post a guild policy regarding VP. I’ve yet to see another guild leader post their raid policies on public forums. The server spoke so clearly back in June that everyone on Prexus got the message. We were obeying the will of the people by leaving well enough alone...no issues have come up until this incident. We had not even been back into VP until this week and were the unwilling participants of a 2-raid zone. Clearly if you (all of the guilds involved) don’t speak to your wizards / monk / cleric you support this idea. I’m not asking for any disciplinary action or anything of that nature just some courtesy. Some members of Infinitus Vindicat went into VP back in June and some of those people now reside in Infinite Vision but the new guild only has 2 of the former guilds officers. We are a new guild with new leadership and new ideas. <br>
Now to this most recent incident in VP. I was not there but I have read most of the posts by those involved and I will add my thoughts to the fray. <br>
First of all I don’t think the MB team knew there was a raid there when the FIRST MB team member zoned in but it was quite evident that there was a CR in progress and a simple /who surely showed at least 3-4 people in the zone already. NO other members of team should have zoned in. That should have been the end of it right there. That they chose to do so anyway shows the ill intent. Call it greed or revenge or whatever but the rest of the team had sufficient time to call it off but did not. <br>
Secondly, Team MB decided to pull a dragon on top of my guildmates. I don’t care how good they are or how good the monk is sometimes things just don’t go like you plan. Things happen. Everyone playing has seen &quot;ghosting&quot; and poor mob pathing. A bit of lag for the monk or a trigger happy Wiz or a host of other things could have caused something to glitch and they could have wiped the entire guild standing in the pull spot.  That was poor gaming in its worst form. That was training. Shame on you Team MB. I wish you no ill but I would ask that you act with a bit more consideration for your fellow gamer next time. <br>
Finally, and this is for Maddie. Backalley is an Officer of Infinite Vision. He does not make guild policy. He is not the &quot;Leader&quot; of Infinite Vision. He is a very strong personality and has his opinions. The fact that he believes VP should be FCFS does not make it so. The community reaction to the raid in June shows that. I would hope that you &quot;LEAD&quot; by example and follow those rules. Justifying the MB Team being in VP last week by saying that Backalley did it back in June is forgetting those people who were there this past weekend who were on their first trip to VP or any of those who were not there in June. Take them into consideration before you make your judgements. He is one guy not the entire guild. He stated that those were his opinions, never once did he call it IV`s policy. <br>
<br>
I was adamant that this kind of thing never happen to IV again when I agreed to accept the vote for me to take the lead role in my guild. NOT stepping on people was one of my main concerns.<br>
<br>
IV`s policy is that VP is a one raid zone. Actions speak louder than words and our actions SINCE THE REFORMATION show we agree with this server observed position. If the server decides that this is no longer an issue we will abide by that as well.<br>
